channel.title: Extracting the Cache
channel.description:
Umm im really new to rsps and am trying to make my own. I have downloaded the Source and Client to a server and know i need the cache. I still havent download the cache and im wondering where i put it. And do i extract it straight into there from winrar?
Thanks

item.title: Extracting the Cache
item.dc:creator: @Jr_Satan Jr Satan
item.description:
@Jr_Satan wrote:

just for future refrence C:/ is not just for rsps it is your main computer C Drive i advise not messing around in there if you don’t understand it. just use it for rsps caches etc i do not advise deleting anything either or you could completly destroy your computer/laptop lol

Read full topic

item.title: Extracting the Cache
item.dc:creator: @TempahScape TempahScape
item.description:
@TempahScape wrote:

on your start menu on your computer click my computer, then you will see something saying SOMETHING (C:).

Thats where you extract it to. need any more help just ask me.
